### `POST /api/v1/oracle/brief` · `oracle.py → oracle_brief()`
Calls `build_oracle_payload(brief)` → Groq Llama 3.3 70B.

**Oracle payload (what NYX sees):**
```
macro_regime:   { regime, inflation_score, growth_score, long_penalty, short_penalty }
fed:            { current_range, next_meeting, days_away, terminal_bps }
economic_veto:  { next_event, hours_away, tier }
nowcast:        { cpi_mom, core_cpi_mom, pce_mom, core_pce_mom, cpi_yoy }
pre_signals:    { adp, gdpnow, jobless_claims, pmi, current_account, umich_sentiment, umich_expectations }
kill_chain:     { alert_level, layers_active, confidence_cap, mismatches, narrative, layer_1..3 }
derivatives:    { gex_regime, total_gex, put_wall, call_wall, spot, cot_spec_net/side/divergent, max_pain, gamma_flip, distance_from_max_pain, top_walls, ema_200, confluence_zones, next_above/below }
opportunities:  { squeeze_candidates: [...top3] }
hidden_hands:   { politician_cluster, hot_tickers, insider_net_usd, fed_tone, hawk/dove_count, divergence_boost }
squeeze:        { has_signal, score, short_interest_pct, days_to_cover, volume_ratio, price_change_5d }
```

### `POST /api/v1/oracle/event-brief` · `oracle.py → oracle_event_brief()`
Input: `{ event_name, event_data: {actual, signal, surprise, slug}, brief }`. Internal `/brief/master` fallback fetch. 90s TTL cache.
Output: `{ summary, trade_implication, risk_level, confidence, generated_at }`

### `POST /api/v1/oracle/analyze` · `oracle.py → oracle_analyze()`
Input: `OracleRequest` with `brief` + `kill_chain_snapshot`. KC drill-down per-signal.

