## 13. KILL CHAIN INPUTS vs AVAILABLE DATA

### GEX Scorer (`gex_scorer.py`) — Reads:
| Input | Source | Rule |
|---|---|---|
| `total_gex` | GEXCalculator | STRONG_NEGATIVE (>10B) |
| `gamma_regime` | GEXCalculator | POSITIVE/NEGATIVE classification |
| `gamma_flip` | GEXCalculator | Above/below flip slug |
| `spot_price` | GEXCalculator | Distance calcs |
| `max_pain` | GEXCalculator | Gravity pull: NEG + spot > max_pain → +1 |
| `ema_200` | PivotCalculator | Pinned between EMA-200 and confluence → no edge |
| `next_above` | PivotCalculator | Confluence ceiling |
| `VIX` | yfinance ^VIX | Context only (stored, no boost rule) |
| `SPY SI%` | yfinance info | squeeze_score ≥ 60 → -10 confidence penalty |
| `cot_boost` | COT scorer (passed in) | STRONG_NEG + COT EXTREME → +2 boost |

### Kill Chain Engine (5 Internal Layers):
`fedwatch, dark_pool (StockgridClient), cot (CFTC), gex (CBOE), sec_13f (EDGAR)`

> ⚠️ KC runs its OWN internal Stockgrid/COT/GEX fetches — this data is NOT the same as `/brief/master` data and NOT shared with Oracle.

### Signals Pipeline (`_inject_kill_chain`):
Economic veto: ≤0.5h → BLOCKED, ≤2h → cap 35%, ≤6h → 50%, ≤24h → 55%
BOOST: +15 conf. HARD_VETO: -30 conf (floor 20). NEUTRAL/SOFT_VETO: cap 65%.
Macro regime: STAGFLATION → long_penalty applied.
Direction mismatch: warning annotation.
Regime gate: Tier 4 → ALL suppressed. Tier 3 → no LONGs unless conf≥60.

